reviews.text:
Unhealthy Japanese slow food. Portions are really small and expensive, waiting long time for the food will make your clothes smell oily from all the steam of the open kitchen. 
Food is also really delicious!

What a poor experience, we come here as we read all the comment , but after 50 min of waiting for the first dishes I gave up 
On table who come 15 min after us get 4 dishes in this lap time 
One table who come after 45 min get 3 dishes like straight away... anyway don’t want to describe all the night but I just feel is not a place for foreigners.. really disappointed

The only restaurant I’ve ever been disappointed enough in my experience to leave an online review. While I have visited the restaurant once before with my Asian colleagues and was aware that the waiting time for food was quite long, this time I returned with my partner and we waited one hour before receiving a plate of grilled mushrooms - only one of the four dishes we ordered. It was at this point we realised that the tables which had ordered after us were receiving all of their food before us. It was clear that if you are not Japanese or do not know the chefs, you will not be treated with the same level of service as the other patrons. After waiting for an hour and a half, we had to cancel the rest of our order. While I could forgive the slowness of the service, it was the feeling of being blatantly discriminated against that made this restaurant  the worst I’ve ever experienced, and left me horrified enough to leave an online review.
This shop open till late on weekends, good for late night snacks

Food is made fresh in front of you here and tastes great.  I particularly like the ox tongue with yuzu.  Okonomiyaki is authentic and great with potato and cheese. However, they took a long time to cook my okonomiyaki, perhaps because there were many orders in front of us.  It was the first thing we ordered but last thing we ate.  Prices are also pretty reasonable here.
